<subSubSection pageId="27" pageNumber="28" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1436,615,1144]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1084,1108]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
This is one of the most common sergestids in 
<collectingRegion box="[862,975,1084,1108]" country="United States of America" name="California" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">California</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[1036,1124,1084,1108]" country="United States of America" name="Oregon" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Oregon</collectingRegion>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Cowles, D. L." box="[1136,1305,1084,1108]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" pagination="247 - 257" refId="ref220091" refString="Cowles, D. L. (1994) Swimming dynamics of the mesopelagic vertically migrating penaeid shrimp Sergestes similis: modes and speeds of swimming. Journal of Crustacean Biology, 14, 247 - 257." type="journal article" year="1994">Cowles (1994)</bibRefCitation>
provided a detailed account of its swimming behavior.
</paragraph>
